entry.title: The Minecraft Hacker That CRASHED a COUNTRY

media:group.media:title: The Minecraft Hacker That CRASHED a COUNTRY
media:group.media:description: In January of 2022, the SquidCraft Games were set to become one of the most popular events in the history of gaming. While everything was going as smoothly, on the fourth day, everything fell apart: 10 players in the tournament suddenly disappeared after a viewer DDoSed their home country of Andorra. In today's episode of Minecraft Uncovered, we'll be exploring the story of the SquidCraft Games, and how/why a Minecraft hacker managed to take down the internet of Andorra. Thanks to ManaCube for sponsoring the video! They're my favorite parkour server and have a ton of other fun games on the network, so definitely check them out :) IP: mcbyt.manacube.com Discord: https://discord.gg/rY4unvn Twitter: https://twitter.com/mcbytt Texture pack: https://youtu.be/69jgFjPkex4 bye love u

entry.title: The Minecraft Hacker That KILLED Hypixel

media:group.media:title: The Minecraft Hacker That KILLED Hypixel
media:group.media:description: Back in June of 2020, Minecraft multiplayer was rocked by a wave of DDoS attacks crashing nearly every major server there was. The perpetrator went by TheTalkingBear, and after he disappeared later that month, everything went back to normal. However, just two days ago, TheTalkingBear made his return to the community with a statement: shutting down the entirety of Hypixel Studios. Today, we'll be taking a look at the Minecraft bear that hacked Hypixel. 0:00 - Introduction. 0:57 - A quick recap. 3:12 - What happened to Hypixel? 7:34 - Who hacked Hypixel, and why? 11:25 - Outro. Discord: https://discord.gg/rY4unvn Twitter: https://twitter.com/mcbytt Texture pack: https://youtu.be/69jgFjPkex4 bye love u

media:group.media:description: Last month, we dived into the decade-old mysteries of Disc 11 & 13. Apparently, Mojang wasn't done just yet. entry.title: MANACUBE: The Rise of an Empire

media:group.media:title: MANACUBE: The Rise of an Empire
media:group.media:description: Today, ManaCube is one of the largest Minecraft servers still around, but its launch in 2013 wasn't as glamorous or easy as you might think. It's been a long journey with some struggle along the way, but ManaCube has come out on top. So, in today's episode of Minecraft Uncovered, let's take a look at the history of one of our favorite networks and see how ManaCube has become a modern empire of Minecraft multiplayer.
